Description. Male ( MCTP ). Carapace orange with dark brown pattern as shown on
Fig. 130
. Chelicerae orange with median longitudinal brown stripe. Pedipalps orange with prolateral brown stains. Labium orange with large brown stain at base. Endites orange. Sternum pale yellow with brown irregular markings, in front of each coxae and in the center. Legs orange, except patella brown. Femora I-IV with pair of ventral longitudinal brown stripes. Tibiae I-IV with dark brown extremities and a median longitudinal mark. Abdomen gray with black pattern (
Fig. 130
). Total length 3.8 . Carapace slightly domed, 2.0 long, 1.5 wide. Eye diameters: PME 0.14 , ALE 0.14 , PLE 0.14 . Lateral eyes on a tubercle. Chelicerae with subapical hyaline keel and inconspicuous stridulatory ridges. Labium 0.14 long, 0.24 wide. Sternum 1.04 long, 0.90 wide. Leg measurements: I: femur 4.0, patella 0.5 , tibia 4.3 , metatarsus 5.3 , tarsus 0.7 , total 14.8 ; II: 2.8 , 0.5 , 2.6 , 3.2 , 0.6 , 9.7 ; III: 1.7 , 0.4 , 1.6 , 1.8 , 0.5 , 6.0; IV: 2.7 , 0.5 , 2.3 , 2.6 , 0.6 , 8.7 . Palpal femur with long and slender stridulatory pick on triangular projected socket. Cymbium with single, strong, distal spine (
Figs. 131–132
). Bulb 0.60 long, slightly curved medially, with distal region slightly concave and dorso-ventrally narrow and a prolateral sclerotized process (
Figs. 132–133
). Abdomen 1.8 long, 1.2 wide, covered with slender hairs.

Female ( MCTP 6768 ). Coloration pattern as in male. Total length 3.9 . Carapace domed, 2.2 long, 1.7 wide. Eye diameters: PME 0.10 , ALE 0.10 , PLE 0.10 . Lateral eyes on a tubercle. Chelicerae as in male. Labium 0.16 long, 0.24 wide. Sternum 0.96 long, 0.80 wide. Leg measurements: I: femur 3.5 , patella 0.6 , tibia 3.7 , metatarsus 4.5 , tarsus 0.8 , total 13.1 ; II: 2.7 , 0.6 , 2.4 , 3.3 , 0.7 , 9.7 ; III: 1.8 , 0.5 , 1.5 , 2.0, 0.6 , 5.8 ; IV: 2.5 , 0.5 , 2.5 , 2.7 , 0.7 , 8.9 . Palpal femur with stridulatory pick as in male. Epigynum with ridged positioning ridges, separated from each other by twice their width (
Fig. 134
). Vulva with large, rounded spermathecae on very thick and short stalks, adjacent to hyaline pockets, anteriorly bent over a large, lateral, sclerotized area (
Fig. 135
). Abdomen 1.7 long, 1.4 wide, as in male.
